## ABLETON LIVE ENGINE DETAILS

### Architecture Knowledge (learned inside-out)
- Live Object Model: 10 core classes (Application, Song, Track, ClipSlot, Clip,
  Device, DeviceParameter, Scene, RackDevice, MixerDevice + sub-types)
- Session View: clip×scene matrix, launch quantization, follow actions
- Arrangement View: linear timeline, cue points, automation lanes
- Device chain: MIDI FX → Instrument → Audio FX → Mixer
- Routing: Input/Output types, Send/Return buses, Resampling
- Rack system: Instrument/Audio/Drum/MIDI racks with chains + macros
- ALS format: gzipped XML containing full project state
- Python API: `import Live` → `song = app.get_document()` → full R/W access
- Max for Live: Python scripts inside M4L devices control entire LOM
- MIDI Remote Scripts: Python scripts for hardware controller integration
- TuningSystem: Custom micro-tuning, reference_pitch, note_tunings in cents
- Ableton Link: Network tempo/beat sync protocol

